claim.claim-text:
1. A method for recovering metal values from crushed refractory sulfide ore, the method comprising:
a. separating the crushed refractory sulfide ore into a fines fraction and a coarse fraction;
b. utilizing the coarse fraction to form a heap;
c. adding refractory sulfide mineral concentrate to the heap;
d. biooxidizing the ore in the heap, including the added refractory sulfide mineral concentrate;
e. recovering metal values from the solution used to biooxidize the ore; and
f. producing refractory sulfide mineral concentrate from the fines fraction.
